Subject: Re: [T2] Adjusting flaps/thermostat when in a warm climate?

Adjust it at night per the bentley book and you'll be fine.  It really 
starts expanding around 100 degrees anyways, so I don't think it's 
really that big of a deal.

Now, if it's not compressing all the way, you might also have a bad 
thermostat...

Mike

